Newly crowned Miss Universe Zozibini Tunzi has accepted Oprah Winfrey's invite to speak at her Leadership Academy For Girls in South Africa. Soon after Zozi was crowned the new Miss Universe, Oprah reached to her on Twitter, extending an invite for her to speak at the academy. The queen of talk was touched by Zozi's speeches and answers during the pageant, which resulted in her extending the invite. She wrote: "Congratulations Miss South Africa, the new Miss UniverseÂ @zozitunzi! Agree with you...leadership is the most powerful thing we should be teaching young women today. We welcome your visit to #OWLAG, our Leadership Academy for Girls". Zozi responded: "I am honored to get and to accept the invite. I can't wait to get the pleasure of meeting you one day. Thank you so much". 